The paper deals with finding an optimal prefix code with a specific length restriction, which is a problem related to information theory (cs.IT). The algorithm proposed in the paper is based on dynamic programming, which is a common technique used in data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.DC). The paper also mentions applications to encoding and decoding lossless codes, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper introduces modifications to the approach that solve other prefix coding problems, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG).
